  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. This package carries a model-version drift weakener: the primary ValidationResult was generated by ModelConfiguration ansys-cfx-24-build-2024q3 (modelVersion 2024-q3-build-2), which predates the UofA's registered currentModelVersion 2026-q1-build-7 by over five solver release cycles. The supporting evidence therefore no longer applies to the model of record.",
